6 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 360.2 of Title 57, unless there
8 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 A. The Department of Corrections shall provide to each
10 wrongfully imprisoned person information that includes:
11 1. A copy of Section 154 of Title 51 of the Oklahoma Statutes
12 which sets forth the extent of liability of the state and its
13 political subdivisions for wrongful criminal felony convictions and
14 imprisonment pursuant to The Governmental Tort Claims Act; and
15 2. A list of and contact information for nonprofit advocacy
16 groups, identified by the Department, that assist persons upon
17 release from a penal institution.
18 B. The Department shall provide the information:
19 1. At the time of the release of the wrongfully imprisoned
20 person from a penal institution; or
21 2. As soon as practicable after the Department has reason to
22 believe that the person is entitled to compensation.
