1 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3218.7-2 of Title 70, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. Within The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education or the
5 system of career technology districts, no resident tuition,
6 nonresident tuition, room and board, and any mandatory fees
7 associated with such attendance shall be charged to:
8 1. A person who was wrongfully incarcerated and awarded
9 compensation pursuant to the provisions of subsection B of Section
10 154 of title 51; and
11 2. Children of any person wrongfully incarcerated and the
12 person was awarded compensation pursuant to the provisions of
13 subsection B of Section 154 of title 51.
14 B. Such waiver of resident tuition, nonresident tuition, room
15 and board, and mandatory fees associated with such attendance shall
16 be limited to one hundred twenty (120) credit hours.
17 C. As used in this section, the term "children" includes
18 children by birth and by adoption.
